{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4fd38df7-4c51-4550-8592-38e416ed29c2","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the MTP runner package:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.0.1\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable.\n\nThe `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest. Make sure your `xunit` package (2.9.3) is compatible — it is, as MTP runner support was added for xUnit v2 2.8.0+.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"36d4295a-0f5c-42f1-a67f-4b291459c79e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":308,"requestId":"3407:386D1F:55F4686:5E11EBC:69F3FA8A"},"id":"46ea0802-1b07-4d01-b788-6a040eb316c6","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:57:53.456Z","parentId":"213bdd43-1a7d-4bb8-b5d4-381899a4a5cd"}
